comment.shortText: Creates a new list by making a copy of an existing list.
comment.returns:
New duplicated list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
copy = List.Copy(list)

Expected value of copy is [1,2,3].

comment.shortText:
Creates a new list of integer numbers between two bounds.
Lower bound is inclusive and upper bound is exclusive.
comment.returns:
New list.

Example:

list = List.FromRange(0,5)

Expected value of list is [0,1,2,3,4].

comment.shortText:
Adds an item to the end of a list.
If item is a list, the entire list will be appended as one item.
comment.returns:
New list with added item.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
append = List.append(list,4)

Expected value of list is [1,2,3,4].

comment.shortText:
Adds an item to the front of a list.
If the item is a list, the entire list will be appended as one item.
comment.returns:
New list with added item.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
append = List.appendFront(list,4)

Expected value of list is [4,1,2,3].

comment.shortText:
Adds items (from a list) to the end of an list.
Items are added to list individually as seperate items.
comment.returns:
List with added items.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
list2 = [9,0]
extend = List.extend(list,list2)

Expected value of extend is [1,2,3,9,0].

comment.shortText:
Adds items (from a list) to the front of an list.
Items are added to list individually as seperate items.
comment.returns:
List with added items.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
list2 = [9,0]
extend = List.extend(list,list2)

Expected value of extend is [9,0,1,2,3].

comment.shortText: Flattens an n-dimensional list into a one-dimensional list.
comment.returns:
Flattened list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3,[4,5]]
flatten = List.flatten(list)

Expected value of list is [1,2,3,4,5].

comment.shortText: Returns the number of items in an list.
comment.returns:
Length of the list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
len = List.len(list)

Expected value of len is 3.

comment.shortText: Removes the item at the specified index from a list.
comment.returns:
List with item removed.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
remove = List.removeIndex(list,1)

Expected value of list is [1,3].

comment.text: Zero-based index number of item to remove.

comment.shortText: Removes items that match specified value from a list. Items must match both the value and type of specified value
comment.text: Returns original list if no items in list match specified value.
comment.returns:
List with item removed

Example:

list = [1,2,2,3]
remove = List.removeValue(list,2,true)

Expected value of list is [1,3].

comment.text:
Removes all instances of specified value if true, removes only the first instance if
     false.

comment.shortText: Reverses the order of items in an list.
comment.returns:
New reversed list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
result = List.reverse(list)

Expected value of result is [3,2,1].

comment.shortText: Creates a copy of a portion of a list, from start index to end index (end not included).
comment.returns:
A new list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3,4,5]
result = List.slice(list,1,3)

Expected value of result is [2,3].

comment.text:
Zero-based index at which to begin slicing.
     A negative index can be used, indicating an offset from the end of the sequence.
     If start is undefined, slice begins from index 0.

Zero-based index before which to end slicing. Slice extracts up to but not including end.
     A negative index can be used, indicating an offset from the end of the sequence.
     If end is undefined, slice extracts through the end of the sequence.

comment.shortText: Sorts a list of strings alphabetically. If items are not strings, they are treated as strings.
comment.text:
Items are sorted according to string Unicode code points (character by character, numbers before upper case
alphabets, upper case alphabets before lower case alphabets)
comment.returns:
New sorted list.

Example:

list = ["1","2","10","Orange","apple"]
sort = List.sortAlpha(list)

Expected value of list is ["1","10","2","Orange","apple"].

comment.shortText:
Sorts a list of numbers in ascending order.
The list must contain numbers.
comment.returns:
New sorted list.

Example:

list = [56,6,48]
sort = List.sortNum(list)

Expected value of list is [6,48,56].

comment.shortText: Adds and/or removes items to/from a list.
comment.text: If no items_to_add are specified, then items are only removed. If num_to_remove is 0, then items are only added.
comment.returns:
A new list.

Example:

list = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]
result = List.splice(list, 1, 3, [2.2, 3.3])

Expected value of result is [10, 2.2, 3.2, 50].

comment.text: Zero-based index at which to add/remove items. (Items are added/removed after specified index)

comment.shortText: Extrudes a polyline according to a specified vector to create a polymesh
comment.text:
Pline is moved by the specified vector and straight line segments are created between the vertices of the input pline and moved pline. The resulting straight line segments and the straight line segments of the input and moved plines are used to define the edges of four-sided polygons. The polygons are joined to create a polymesh
If cap is true, input pline and moved pline are used as edges to create two polygons. The polygones are joined to the polymesh from above.
comment.returns: Polymesh created from extrusion

Closes polymesh by creating a polygon on each end of the extrusion if true

comment.shortText: Checks if a string contains a specified search string.
comment.returns:
True if str contains search_str, false otherwise.

Example:

string = "Orange"
incl = String.includes(string,"an")
Expected value of incl is true.

comment.shortText: Returns the number of characters in a string.
comment.returns:
Length of string.

Example:

string = "Orange"
length = String.len(string)
Expected value of length is 6.

comment.shortText:
Searches for and replaces the specified search string in a string.
The search string can also be a regular expression.
comment.returns:
New string with replaced characters.

Example:

string = "Orange"
newString = String.Replace(string,"O","Ar")
Expected value of newString is "Arrange".

comment.text: Sub-string or regular expression to search for.

comment.shortText:
Returns the position index of the first occurance of the specified search string within a string.
If the specified sub-string cannot be found, then returns -1.
comment.returns:
Number that represents position of search_str in str.

Example:

string = "Orange"
search = String.search(string,"e")
Expected value of search is 5.

comment.text: Sub-string or regular expression to search for.

comment.shortText: Splits a string into a list of substrings using a specified separator string.
comment.returns:
List of substrings.

Example:

string = "Orange"
split = String.split(string,"a")
Expected value of split is ["Or","nge"].

comment.text: String of characters used to split string.

comment.shortText: Checks if a string starts with the specified start string.
comment.returns:
True if str starts with search_str, false otherwise.

Example:

string = "Orange"
result = String.startsWith(string,"Or")
Expected value of result is true.

comment.shortText:
Extracts characters in a string between two specified indices and returns it as a new string.
Start index is inclusive and end index is exclusive.
comment.returns:
New string with extracted characters.

Example:

string = "Orange"
substring = String.substring(string,1,4)
Expected value of ends is "ran".

comment.text: Zero-based index to start extracting characters (inclusive).
Zero-based index to stop extracting characters (exclusive).
